<!-- Appendices Section -->

<h2 id="assumptions">A. Assumptions</h2>
<p>
  The following assumptions were made in the development of this report:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Energy and water costs are based on current utility rates and are subject to change.</li>
  <li>Implementation costs are estimates based on industry standards and may vary depending on the specific equipment selected and installation conditions.</li>
  <li>Energy and water savings are estimates based on engineering calculations and may vary depending on actual operating conditions and occupant behavior.</li>
  <li>The building will continue to be operated and maintained in a manner consistent with current practices.</li>
  <li>Equipment will be replaced at the end of its useful life.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="equations">B. Equations:</h2>
<p>
  The following equations were used in the development of this report:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Simple Payback Period:</strong> Implementation Cost ÷ Annual Cost Savings</li>
  <li><strong>Return on Investment (ROI):</strong> (Annual Cost Savings ÷ Implementation Cost) × 100%</li>
  <li><strong>Net Present Value (NPV):</strong> Sum of the present value of future cash flows - Initial investment</li>
  <li><strong>Internal Rate of Return (IRR):</strong> Discount rate that makes the NPV of all cash flows equal to zero</li>
  <li><strong>Energy Use Intensity (EUI):</strong> Annual Energy Use ÷ Gross Floor Area</li>
  <li><strong>Water Use Intensity (WUI):</strong> Annual Water Use ÷ Gross Floor Area</li>
</ul>

