<h2 id="equivalent-full-load-hours">D. Equivalent Full Load Hours (EFLH)</h2>
<p>
  The following equivalent full load hours were used in the energy calculations:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Cooling:</strong> {{#if coolingEFLH}}{{coolingEFLH}}{{else}}1,200{{/if}} hours per year</li>
  <li><strong>Heating:</strong> {{#if heatingEFLH}}{{heatingEFLH}}{{else}}800{{/if}} hours per year</li>
  <li><strong>Lighting:</strong> {{#if lightingEFLH}}{{lightingEFLH}}{{else}}3,000{{/if}} hours per year</li>
  <li><strong>Ventilation:</strong> {{#if ventilationEFLH}}{{ventilationEFLH}}{{else}}4,000{{/if}} hours per year</li>
  <li><strong>Domestic Hot Water:</strong> {{#if dhwEFLH}}{{dhwEFLH}}{{else}}2,000{{/if}} hours per year</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="additional-o-m">E. Additional O&M</h2>
<p>
  The following additional operation and maintenance recommendations are provided:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Develop and implement a preventive maintenance program for all building systems.</li>
  <li>Train facility staff on proper operation and maintenance of building systems.</li>
  <li>Implement a system for tracking and addressing occupant comfort complaints.</li>
  <li>Regularly review and optimize building automation system setpoints and schedules.</li>
  <li>Conduct periodic recommissioning of building systems to ensure continued optimal performance.</li>
</ul>

